title.$t: NAD Responds to Community Discussion on Governor Daugaard

media$title.$t: NAD Responds to Community Discussion on Governor Daugaard

media$description.$t:
The NAD responds to the outpouring of concern, opposition and support surrounding the community discussion on Governor Daugaard. 

To learn more about the NAD, its mission and objectives, visit http://www.nad.org. 

To learn more about our 51st Biennial Conference on July 3 - 7, 2012 in Louisville, Kentucky, visit http://www.nad.org/louisville. 

As always, we welcome your comments, and we hope to see you in Louisville!

title.$t: NAD Spring Benefit Gala - Our Deaf Children

media$title.$t: NAD Spring Benefit Gala - Our Deaf Children

media$description.$t:
The National Association of the Deaf (NAD) is pleased to announce the second annual NAD Spring Benefit Gala set to take place on Saturday, May 14 at the beautiful Hotel Shattuck Plaza in Berkeley, California from 5:00 to 10:00 pm. The theme of this year's gala is "Celebrating a New Era of Leadership" in recognition of new leadership at the NAD with incoming Chief Executive Officer (CEO), Howard Rosenblum.

The evening will conclude with a live auction for one-on-one breakfast the following morning with NAD leaders and celebrities in attendance.

Join us for an elegant evening, cocktail hour & three course dinner with wine. Your participation will benefit and sustain the tireless work of the NAD on behalf of the American deaf and hard of hearing community.

Individual gala tickets are $150.00 per person ($75 is tax-deductible). "Invest in the Future of NAD" with an additional $50 donation (and receive a badge to wear at the Gala). Click here to purchase 2011 NAD Spring Benefit Gala tickets. Tickets on sale until Monday, May 9, 2011.

Check http://www.nad.org/gala frequently for 2011 NAD Spring Benefit Gala updates.

title.$t: The Preservation of Sign Language by George W. Veditz

media$title.$t: The Preservation of Sign Language by George W. Veditz

media$description.$t: "Preservation" is a two-minute film featuring George W. Veditz, onetime president of the National Association of the Deaf (NAD) of the United States, demonstrating in sign language the importance of defending the right of deaf people to their language. This film was selected to the National Film Registry at the U.S. Library of Congress in 2010. Thanks to the Gallaudet Archive for preserving this video: http://videocatalog.gallaudet.edu/player.cfm?video=2520.
